Blog list backend using Node.js .
Added blog entries are associated with user currently logged in.
Uses token based authentication for user administration. (Description)[https://fullstackopen.com/en/part4/token_authentication]

# Used environment variables
* MONGODB_URI : full url of MongoDB database that stores the data.
* PORT : The tco/ip port where the backend should be accessible. Frontend usually tries to use port 3003
* SECRET : used by jwt library to create user token when user is logging in.
